湖南援鄂护士在武汉金银潭医院ICU五日记丨新冠肺炎亲历。
Nurse Hubei in Hunan experienced ICU 5 diary in Wuhan Gold and Silver Pool Hospital.
作者：刘颂辉 来源：中国经营网。
Author: Liu Songhui Source: China Management Network.
本报记者 刘颂辉 上海报道“在前往武汉之前，我做好充足的准备接受各种困难，然而当我真正融入到武汉疫情战役后才发现，从疫情发生到现在，还坚持在岗位的武汉前线医务人员有多么不容易。
"Before leaving for Wuhan, I was fully prepared to accept all kinds of difficulties, but when I really integrated into the Wuhan epidemic campaign, I found that from the outbreak of the epidemic until now, still adhere to the Wuhan front-line medical staff is not easy.
”在武汉市金银潭医院重症监护室驰援的第三天，中南大学湘雅二医院血液净化中心护士刘亮写下这样一段话。
"Liu Liang, a nurse at the Xiangya II Hospital of Hunan University, wrote this on the third day of assistance from the intensive care unit of Wuhan Gold and Silver Pool Hospital.
新型冠状病毒感染肺炎疫情爆发以后，刘亮和4名血液净化护士组成的国家医疗队从湖南长沙出发，驰援疫情防疫工作。
After the outbreak of the new coronavirus pneumonia, Liu Liang and four blood purification nurses from the national medical team set out from Changsha, Hunan, to help epidemic prevention work.
这支平均年龄在28岁的医疗队，仅在20分钟时间里就完成了快速招募。
The team, with an average age of 28, completed rapid recruitment in just 20 minutes.
他们中有人忙于医疗救援被汗水浸湿衣服，有人在ICU病房里度过了30岁生日。
Some of them were too busy with medical assistance to get their clothes soaked in sweat, and others spent their 30th birthday in the ICU ward.
1月31日，《中国经营报》记者试图采访刘亮及他的同事，但由于医务工作繁忙，并未成功。
On January 31, the China Business Daily tried to interview Liu Liang and his colleagues, but was unsuccessful because of heavy medical work.
不过，记者从医院方面获取了其每天写下的一线日记。
However, the reporter from the hospital side of his daily written a first-line diary.
（刘亮护士在武汉市金银潭医院。
Nurse Liu Liang is at Jintan Hospital in Wuhan.
）摘口罩2小时仍留压痕由中南大学湘雅二医院组成的援鄂医疗队5名护士分别是主管护师侯亦平（队长）、主管护师黄艳清、护师李婉贞、护师钟晓平、护师刘亮。
The five nurses of the medical team in Xiangya II Hospital of Zhongnan University were supervisor Hou Yiping (team leader), supervisor Huang Yanqing, nurse Li Wanzhen, nurse Xiaoping Zhong and nurse Liu Liang.
刘亮是该支医疗队中唯一的男护士。
Liu Liang is the only male nurse in the medical team.
1月27日中午12点，5人从长沙出发，赶赴新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情最前沿武汉市金银潭医院。
January 27 12: 00 noon, five people from Changsha, rushed to the new coronavirus infection of the forefront of pneumonia in Wuhan City gold and silver pool hospital.
刘亮被派往支援的是收治病情最重患者的医院南七楼病区。
Liu Liang was assigned to the hospital's south seventh floor ward, where the most serious cases were treated.
报到以后，穿好防护服进入监护室里面，进一步熟悉监护室的环境。
After check-in, put on protective clothing and enter the intensive care unit, further familiar with the environment.
“这里的病人的病情都非常重，病情变化也是非常迅速。
"The patients here are very serious and the condition is very rapid.
”他在日记中写道。
"he wrote in his diary.
1月29日0时~4时，刘亮协同其他医务人员管理四名危重病人，每名病人的床头护理级别都显示醒目的两个字——“特级”，前线医务工作者穿着足足五层厚的衣服来完成抽血、血气分析、打针等各项护理措施。
On January 29, between 0000 and 0400 hours, Liu Liang, together with other medical staff, administered four critically ill patients. Each patient's bedside care level was marked with the word "super-standard," and front-line medical workers wore full five-storey cloths to complete nursing interventions such as blood extraction, blood gas analysis, and injections.
同时，还需要时刻保持警惕呼吸机、监护仪上的数据。
At the same time, we need to be on the alert ventilator, monitor data.
谈及在医院重症监护室的工作，刘亮记录道：“6个小时过去，脱下防护服，感觉轻松了好多，这才发现，防护服真的好闷！对着手机镜头整理头发时发现，脸颊上口罩带子的压痕还在，这时我摘下口罩已经差不多过去2个小时了。
Speaking about work in the intensive care unit of the hospital, Liu Liang noted: "Six hours later, when I took off my protective clothing and felt much better, it was really stuffy. When I straightened up my hair, I found the pressure mark on my cheek mask was still there.
”1月29日下午4点，刘亮在支援队医务人员的指导下管理5名患者，在厚厚的防护服下不停歇工作四个小时。
At 4 p.m. on January 29, Liu Liang supervised five patients under the guidance of medical staff of the support team and worked for four hours without interruption under heavy protective clothing.
“一切细小的动作都变得如此困难，尿不湿似乎都是多余的，汗水早已经湿透衣服。
"Everything becomes so difficult that it seems superfluous to urinate and sweat has soaked through your clothes.
”他回忆道。
'he recalled.
在ICU度过30岁生日新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情牵动着全国人民的心，湖南有一大批医务工作者逆向挺进最危险的地方湖北省武汉市，开展医疗援助。
The pneumonia epidemic linked to the new coronavirus infection on the 30th birthday of the ICU has shaken the hearts and minds of people across the country.Hunan has a large number of medical workers who march backwards into Wuhan, the most dangerous place in the province, to provide medical assistance.
“下午6点，我完成了今天的值班任务。
"At 6 p.m., I finished my duty for today.
脱下厚厚的防护服，走出隔离病区的时候，突然想起来今天是自己30岁的生日。
As he took off his thick protective clothing and walked out of the quarantine zone, it suddenly occurred to him that it was his 30th birthday.
走在院区里，我在心中默默许下今年的生日愿望：愿疫情早日结束，愿所有的患者都能康复，愿所有医务人员都能平安回家！”1月29日，中南大学湘雅二医院血液净化中心主管护师候亦平在生日这天的工作地点是武汉市金银潭医院南六楼病区的重症监护室，主要工作是为患者进行连续性肾脏替代治疗（CRRT）。
As I walked in the courtyard, I silently made a wish in my heart for this year's birthday: May the epidemic end soon and all the patients recover and all medical staff return home safely!
据同行的主管护师黄艳清介绍，在医院，医护人员各有分工，更多的事则相互协作。
According to the supervisor's nurse Huang Yanqing, in the hospital, the medical staff have their own division of labor, more things work together.
医生看见护士工作忙，就会帮着采集动脉血做血气分析，一起帮忙给病人翻身拍背，给病人喂食。
Doctors see nurses busy, will help collect arterial blood for blood gas analysis, together to help patients turn over the back, feeding patients.
同事之间也会相互关注防护服有没有穿戴好，有没有吃饭等等。
Colleagues will also pay attention to each other whether the protective clothing is well dressed, there are no meals, etc.
事实上，早在1月25日晚，湖南省首批援助医疗队乘坐高铁前往湖北。
Indeed, as early as the night of January 25, the first aid teams from Hunan Province traveled to Hubei by high-speed rail.
医疗人员共计137人，其中有43名医生和93名护理人员。
The total number of medical personnel was 137, of whom 43 were doctors and 93 paramedics.
据湖南省卫健委官网披露，1月29日，湖南省迅速集结首支援助湖北应对新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎国家中医医疗队预备队。
On January 29, Hunan Province quickly assembled its first reserve team of Chinese medicine doctors to help Hubei deal with a new coronavirus infection, according to Hunan Health Officers' Web site.
仅仅半天的时间，参与驰援的单位共有700余名医务工作者主动请缨志愿奔赴前线。
In just half a day, more than 700 medical workers volunteered to go to the frontline.
预备队中有8名医生，22名护士。
There are 8 doctors and 22 nurses in the reserve.
队员中最大年龄54岁,最小为22岁。
The oldest of the team members is 54 and the youngest is 22.
1月29日，武汉天气转晴。
The weather turned fine in Wuhan on January 29.
刘亮在日记中写道：“尽管防疫工作强度高，武汉疫情战役已坚持一月有余，金银潭医院的前线战士让我看到国之担当，这似乎比武汉今日的阳光更能温暖人。
"Despite the intensity of the epidemic prevention work, the battle against the epidemic in Wuhan lasted more than a month," Liu wrote in his diary. "The frontline fighters at the Golden and Silver Pool Hospital showed me the responsibility of China.
”（编辑：石英婧 校对：翟军）。
(Editor: Quartz, proofread by Zhai Jun).
